<subSubSection id="346EBF46D3FFB82184FCDF6DE1A68772" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" type="recognition and notes">
<paragraph id="CDB769D6187E0DE785C556101A371F24" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Recognition and notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="48DB21C88814162B0888F5045EF0417F" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName id="EFBFC7620DFD9204B00A1E450F0CD293" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Connaraceae" genus="Rourea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rourea tenuis" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis id="C37271721D77F0D601C2D1A5498C75F5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Rourea tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognised by leaves 5-7-foliolate, leaflets usually elliptic or ovate, abaxially hirsute and inflorescences in thyrses or panicles with glandular trichomes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E8DABA7A07F2FBCEB9645264AF8FF07" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<bibRefCitation id="22A09D1061D21BC66FDFB02AC735D7CF" author="Forero, E" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 119" refId="B10" refString="Forero, E, 1976. A revision of the American species of Rourea subgenus Rourea (Connaraceae). Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 26 (1): 1 - 119" title="A revision of the American species of Rourea subgenus Rourea (Connaraceae)." volume="26" year="1976">Forero (1976)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName id="8D49360F87068CFE1A0937D95FF2C647" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Connaraceae" genus="Rourea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rourea tenuis" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis id="7CE2C2C96EC5D0BEC2CB952F07124917" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Rourea tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="10B7EC9035843F5B2882A646EC1846F5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Connaraceae" genus="Rourea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rourea (R.) subsp. sect." order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Multifoliolatae" species="tenuis" subGenus="R." subSpecies="sect.">Rourea subgen. R. sect. Multifoliolatae</taxonomicName>
mainly due to the long staminal tube, reduced inflorescences and leaflets hairy. Aside from that, this species does not resemble other members of the section in overall similarity of leaves: in 
<taxonomicName id="DE3039AB09826DF8FAEBF9E516ED4618" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. tenuis" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis id="69FD35EC557C7D9838A5F41B86D0D68B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the number of leaflets is reduced and they are usually relatively larger, with elliptic or ovate shape (vs. oblong, narrowly elliptic or narrowly ovate) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B575072AE46024172E52E650F38C5C4E" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Leaves in Rourea subgen. R. sect. Multifoliolatae: A R. discolor B R. martiana C R. tenuis D R. cnestidifolia." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.169.54297.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/484418" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">1C</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="5BC68C2ED4E9626EC4C1FA41B48C807B" author="Forero, E" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 119" refId="B10" refString="Forero, E, 1976. A revision of the American species of Rourea subgenus Rourea (Connaraceae). Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 26 (1): 1 - 119" title="A revision of the American species of Rourea subgenus Rourea (Connaraceae)." volume="26" year="1976">Forero (1976)</bibRefCitation>
firstly noticed that 
<taxonomicName id="626CF61537DD549483FA4AC2BE999772" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. tenuis" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis id="542B2887E814D9AE9CBAFB8E7A8647E2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be a borderline species between those of 
<taxonomicName id="83BAFC79BDE6A3287E1ECC39BFE50E07" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. (R.) subsp. sect." order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="section" section="Multifoliolatae" species="tenuis" subGenus="R." subSpecies="sect.">R. subgen. R. sect. Multifoliolatae</taxonomicName>
with those from the Amazon, then suggested that the morphological limits of the section should be re-evaluated (
<bibRefCitation id="B9586BAAA361C91A84CC3760B0597741" author="Forero, E" journalOrPublisher="Brazilian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="65 - 77" refId="B13" refString="Forero, E, Carbono, E, Vidal, LA, 1984. Nuevas especies de Connaraceae Neotropicales. Revista Brasileira de Botanica. Brazilian Journal of Botany 7 (1): 65 - 77" title="Nuevas especies de Connaraceae Neotropicales. Revista Brasileira de Botanica." volume="7" year="1984">Forero et al. 1984</bibRefCitation>
). The present study, therefore, considers that the circumscription of the whole group should be tested using molecular and phylogenetic approaches.
</paragraph>
